================================================================================
WHEN DO YOU NEED A COMMERCIAL LICENSE?
================================================================================

A commercial license is required if you:

  - Use, embed, or distribute this software as part of a proprietary or
    closed-source product or service
  - Offer this software or a derivative as a managed / hosted service
    without complying with the AGPL-3.0 source disclosure requirement
  - Integrate this software into a product where AGPL-3.0 copyleft would
    propagate to your proprietary code
  - Require dedicated support, SLAs, or custom contractual terms

A commercial license is NOT required if you:

  - Self-host the software for internal use and publish any modifications
    under AGPL-3.0
  - Use the software in an open source project licensed under AGPL-3.0
    compatible terms
  - Evaluate the software for non-production purposes

